{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab2d2884-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8481"},"text":"§ 8481.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Support of athletic and physical fitness programs","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab2d2885-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Authority.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2d2886-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Contracts and cooperative agreements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of the Navy may enter into contracts and cooperative agreements with the Naval Academy Athletic Association for the purpose of supporting the athletic and physical fitness programs of the Naval Academy. Notwithstanding ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3201/e"},"text":"section 3201(e) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary may enter such contracts or cooperative agreements on a sole source basis pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3204/a/5"},"text":"section 3204(a)(5) of this title","children":[],"tail":". Notwithstanding chapter 63 of title 31, a cooperative agreement under this section may be used to acquire property or services for the direct benefit or use of the Naval Academy."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2d2887-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Leases","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may enter into leases, in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2667"},"text":"section 2667 of this title","children":[],"tail":", or licenses with the Association for the purpose of supporting the athletic and physical fitness programs of the Naval Academy. Any such lease or license shall be deemed to satisfy the conditions of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2667/h/2"},"text":"section 2667(h)(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab2d2888-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Use of Navy Personal Property by the Association","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may allow the Association to use, at no cost, personal property of the Department of the Navy to assist the Association in supporting the athletic and physical fitness programs of the Naval Academy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab2d2889-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Acceptance of Support.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2d288a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Support received from the association","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1342"},"text":"section 1342 of title 31","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary may accept from the Association funds, supplies, and services for the support of the athletic and physical fitness programs of the Naval Academy. For purposes of this section, employees or personnel of the Association may not be considered to be employees of the United States."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2d288b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Funds received from ncaa","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may accept funds from the National Collegiate Athletic Association to support the athletic and physical fitness programs of the Naval Academy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2d288c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Limitation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall ensure that contributions under this subsection do not reflect unfavorably on the ability of the Department of the Navy, any of its employees, or any member of the armed forces to carry out any responsibility or duty in a fair and objective manner, or compromise the integrity or appearance of integrity of any program of the Department of the Navy, or any individual involved in such a program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab2f988d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Retention and Use of Funds","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2260/d"},"text":"section 2260(d) of this title","children":[],"tail":", funds received under this section may be retained for use in support of athletic and physical fitness programs of the Naval Academy and shall remain available until expended."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab2f988e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Trademarks and Service Marks.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2f988f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Licensing, marketing, and sponsorship agreements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"An agreement under subsection (a)(1) may, consistent with sections 2260 (other than subsection (d)) and 8022(b)(3) of this title, authorize the Association to enter into licensing, marketing, and sponsorship agreements relating to trademarks and service marks identifying the Naval Academy, subject to the approval of the Department of the Navy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2f9890-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Limitations","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"No such licensing, marketing, or sponsorship agreement may be entered into if it would reflect unfavorably on the ability of the Department of the Navy, any of its employees, or any member of the armed forces to carry out any responsibility or duty in a fair and objective manner, or if the Secretary determines that the use of the trademark or service mark would compromise the integrity or appearance of integrity of any program of the Department of the Navy, or any individual involved in such a program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab2f9891-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Service on Association Board of Control","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Association is a designated entity for which authorization under sections 1033(a) and 1589(a) of this title may be provided.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab2f9892-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Conditions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The authority provided in this section with respect to the Association is available only so long as the Association continues to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2f9893-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/g/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" qualify as a nonprofit organization under section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 and operates in accordance with this section, the laws of the State of Maryland, and the constitution and bylaws of the Association; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab2f9894-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/g/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" operate exclusively to support the athletic and physical fitness programs of the Naval Academy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab2f9895-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8481/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Association Defined","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, the term “Association” means the Naval Academy Athletic Association.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab2f9896-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/dA/tV/s542/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, div. A, title V, § 542(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1735"},"text":"126 Stat. 1735","children":[],"tail":", § 6981; renumbered § 8481 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 807(c)(1), 809(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1836"},"text":"132 Stat. 1836","children":[],"tail":", 1840; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1883/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1883(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4294"},"text":"134 Stat. 4294","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab2f9897-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab2f9898-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idab2f9899-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, referred to in subsec. (g)(1), is classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s501/c/3"},"text":"section 501(c)(3) of Title 26","children":[],"tail":", Internal Revenue Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idab2f989a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 8491 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s9191"},"text":"section 9191 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Prior sections 8495 to 8502 were repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXVI/s1662/f/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XVI, § 1662(f)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2994"},"text":"108 Stat. 2994","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-12-01"},"text":"Dec. 1, 1994","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8495, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/524"},"text":"70A Stat. 524","children":[],"tail":", provided that members of Air National Guard of United States were not in active Federal service except when ordered thereto under law. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12401"},"text":"section 12401 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8496, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/524"},"text":"70A Stat. 524","children":[],"tail":", authorized President to order commissioned officers of Air National Guard of United States to active duty in National Guard Bureau. See section 12402(a), (b)(2) of this title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8497, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/525"},"text":"70A Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":", provided that members of Air National Guard of United States ordered to active duty were to be ordered to duty as Reserves of Air Force. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12403"},"text":"section 12403 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8498, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/525"},"text":"70A Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":", related to organization during initial mobilization of units of Air National Guard of United States ordered into active Federal service. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12404"},"text":"section 12404 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8499, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/525"},"text":"70A Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":", related to application of laws governing Air Force to members of Air National Guard called into Federal service. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12405"},"text":"section 12405 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8500, acts ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/525"},"text":"70A Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/456/dA/tXII/s1234/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–456, div. A, title XII, § 1234(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/2059"},"text":"102 Stat. 2059","children":[],"tail":", authorized President to call Air National Guard units and members into Federal service. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12406"},"text":"section 12406 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8501, acts ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/525"},"text":"70A Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/456/dA/tXII/s1234/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–456, div. A, title XII, § 1234(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/2059"},"text":"102 Stat. 2059","children":[],"tail":", related to period of service and apportionment of members and units of Air National Guard called into Federal service. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12407"},"text":"section 12407 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8502, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/526"},"text":"70A Stat. 526","children":[],"tail":", related to physical examinations of members of Air National Guard called into or mustered out of Federal service. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12408"},"text":"section 12408 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 8503 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s9203"},"text":"section 9203 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section